commentary: Samiullah Shinwari to Mominul Haque, OUT that's gone through Mominul, Shenwari gets rid of the set batsman! He sent down a legspinner around off, Mominul came down the track to drive but missed the line of the ball because of the turn and the ball hit the middle stump. The umpires are checking for the no ball now, no angles are conclusive because there are fielders on either side of the pitch blocking the path of the cameras. So we can't see clearly where the foot lands, but he seems fine and Mominul walks back

commentary: Hamid Hassan to Abdur Razzak, OUT full delivery is driven down the ground and mid-off cuts it to one. Oh wait, he has a direct hit and looks like the batsman was lazy to make his ground. Bowden refers to third umpire. Replays show Razzak did not ground his bat even though he had made it and his bat was in the air when the ball hit the stumps. That's very irresponsible from a player who has played nearly 150 ODIs
